        conseils: "The Bayeux Tapestry (museum, €12) takes 1h30 with the included audioguide — arrive at opening (9am) to avoid queues in summer. Notre-Dame Cathedral is free to enter and deserves 30 minutes. Bayeux market (Saturday mornings, Place Saint-Patrice) is a fine Norman market. For D-Day beaches, the hourly taxi hire is ideal: your driver takes you to Arromanches (Mulberry harbour remains), Omaha Beach and the American Cemetery at Colleville (free, deeply moving). Allow at least half a day for D-Day sites. La Rapière restaurant (Rue Saint-Jean) serves refined Norman cuisine in a medieval setting. The Bayeux War Cemetery is the largest Commonwealth cemetery in France (4,648 graves) and is free to visit.",
